1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:07,000
The building's custodian is on vacation for the month and Dwight is too cheap to hire a replacement.

2
00:00:07,000 --> 00:00:14,000
So instead we're living in filth, but not for long because I have created the chore wheel.

3
00:00:14,000 --> 00:00:17,000
Oh yeah, can I spin first?

4
00:00:17,000 --> 00:00:24,000
Well it doesn't spin, we'll just move the wheel one notch each morning and you see what chore you get that day.

5
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:25,000
A wheel is supposed to spin.

6
00:00:25,000 --> 00:00:34,000
Yeah, you know like guh guh guh no I'm familiar with spinning, it's just that wouldn't work with a chore wheel because people might get the same chore.

7
00:00:34,000 --> 00:00:37,000
Bah, boring. All she talks about is chores.

8
00:00:37,000 --> 00:00:39,000
A wheel wants to spin Pam.

9
00:00:41,000 --> 00:00:43,000
Spinning would be more fun.

10
00:00:46,000 --> 00:00:47,000
Okay.

11
00:00:47,000 --> 00:00:50,000
Okay, that's what I'm talking about!

12
00:00:52,000 --> 00:00:54,000
Big money, big money!

13
00:00:55,000 --> 00:00:56,000
Yeah!

14
00:00:57,000 --> 00:00:58,000
Mug duty.

15
00:00:58,000 --> 00:01:00,000
Yes, you clean all the mugs in the sink.

16
00:01:01,000 --> 00:01:02,000
This sucks.

17
00:01:02,000 --> 00:01:05,000
Yeah, seriously it's like everything on there is work.

18
00:01:05,000 --> 00:01:08,000
I don't think you guys understand why we're doing this.

19
00:01:08,000 --> 00:01:12,000
Yeah, and I don't think that you understand wheels.

20
00:01:13,000 --> 00:01:19,000
I've been through several rounds of development with the team and here's where we stand with the chore wheel.

21
00:01:20,000 --> 00:01:31,000
We've got prizes. Ten bucks, candy bar, manager for an hour, but there are also penalties like no internet, Stanley gets your lunch.

22
00:01:31,000 --> 00:01:36,000
The one thing that is not on the chore wheel is chores, but they were right, it's more fun this way.

23
00:01:42,000 --> 00:01:46,000
Tiny wheel! Tiny wheel! Tiny wheel!

24
00:01:46,000 --> 00:01:51,000
The tiny wheel actually does have chores. It's so cute no one seems to mind.

25
00:01:51,000 --> 00:01:52,000
Toilets!

26
00:01:52,000 --> 00:01:53,000
Toilets!

27
00:02:16,000 --> 00:02:18,000
Pam, we gotta go.

28
00:02:18,000 --> 00:02:21,000
Cece, go back inside. Grandma's got breakfast, okay?

29
00:02:23,000 --> 00:02:26,000
We are going to Roy's wedding.

30
00:02:26,000 --> 00:02:34,000
Yep, Roy. I think the only weird thing about going to your wife's ex-fiance's wedding on a weekday at 8am is that it's your wife's ex-fiance.

31
00:02:34,000 --> 00:02:36,000
Thanks, Mom!

32
00:02:37,000 --> 00:02:38,000
A banana?

33
00:02:38,000 --> 00:02:40,000
Yeah, I'm afraid he's only gonna have hot talks.

34
00:02:40,000 --> 00:02:42,000
Oh, come on, not even Roy will have hot talks.

35
00:02:42,000 --> 00:02:44,000
I planned a wedding with him. He wanted hot dogs.

36
00:02:47,000 --> 00:02:49,000
It's all weird.

37
00:02:50,000 --> 00:02:52,000
Oh, Pete, you've got mail.

38
00:02:52,000 --> 00:02:54,000
Really? I got something?

39
00:02:54,000 --> 00:02:56,000
Well, it's addressed to customer service, so it's your mail.

40
00:02:56,000 --> 00:02:58,000
Well, you know, I'm also customer service.

41
00:02:58,000 --> 00:03:00,000
Yeah, I'm alternating.

42
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:02,000
Yay, another person yelling at me.

43
00:03:02,000 --> 00:03:06,000
Well, it could be a nice letter. I write nice letters to companies all the time.

44
00:03:06,000 --> 00:03:07,000
That's really nice.

45
00:03:07,000 --> 00:03:11,000
Wow, Newsweek, huh? This election thing is crazy, right?

46
00:03:11,000 --> 00:03:13,000
It's open.

47
00:03:13,000 --> 00:03:17,000
Oh, yeah, I accidentally read it. It's not a nice letter.

48
00:03:22,000 --> 00:03:27,000
Get excited. The special projects fairy has arrived.

49
00:03:27,000 --> 00:03:29,000
I know you don't really exist.

50
00:03:29,000 --> 00:03:31,000
I'm sorry, I'm sorry.

51
00:03:31,000 --> 00:03:33,000
I'm sorry, I'm sorry.

52
00:03:33,000 --> 00:03:35,000
The fairy has arrived.

53
00:03:35,000 --> 00:03:37,000
I know you don't really exist.

54
00:03:37,000 --> 00:03:41,000
Today I launched my big charity initiative, Operation Giveback.

55
00:03:41,000 --> 00:03:47,000
Andy has shot down all of my special projects thus far, but this one is about charity,

56
00:03:47,000 --> 00:03:50,000
so I'd like to see him piss on that one.

57
00:03:53,000 --> 00:03:55,000
Daryl!

58
00:03:55,000 --> 00:03:57,000
Oh, what's happening?

59
00:03:57,000 --> 00:03:58,000
Congratulations, baby.

60
00:03:58,000 --> 00:03:59,000
Oh, thank you.

61
00:03:59,000 --> 00:04:01,000
Coconut shrimp.

62
00:04:02,000 --> 00:04:04,000
I told you I'd have it.

63
00:04:04,000 --> 00:04:05,000
Yes, you did.

64
00:04:05,000 --> 00:04:08,000
Oh, you have arrived, sir. Well done.

65
00:04:08,000 --> 00:04:11,000
Roy and I used to work together downstairs in a warehouse.

66
00:04:11,000 --> 00:04:16,000
He used to be engaged to Pam, but then she tossed him aside like a cold-hearted bitch.
